OL,6,F"The decision taken by the Ministry of
OL,7,FHousing, Communities and Local
OL,8,FGovernment to significantly reduce
OL,9,Ffunding aimed at tackling economic
OL,10,Finactivity in 2026/27 is deeply
OL,11,Fconcerning and demonstrates a lack of
OL,12,Funderstanding of local need.
OL,14,F"Minister O'Dowd will continue to
OL,15,Fpress Westminster for a more
OL,16,Fappropriate capital and resource split
OL,17,Fwithin the Local Growth Fund to
OL,18,Fprovide more flexibility to support
OL,19,Fthe Community and Voluntary Sector.
